 most likely carriers of the virus in the wild.The largest recorded outbreak of Ebola virus disease is ongoing in West Africa: more people have been infected in this current outbreak than in all previous outbreaks combined. The current outbreak is also the first to occur in West Africa\u2014which is outside the previously known range of the Ebola virus.Pigott et al. have now updated predictions about where in Africa wild animals may harbour the virus and where the transmission of the virus from these animals to humans is possible. As such, the map identifies the regions that are most at risk of a future Ebola outbreak. The data behind these new maps include the locations of all recorded primary cases of Ebola in human populations\u2014the 'index' cases\u2014many of which have been linked to animal sources. The data also include the locations of recorded cases of Ebola virus infections in wild bats and primates from the last forty years. The maps, which were modelled using more flexible methods than previous predic\u2026", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Pigott, David M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Golding, Nick", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mylne, Adrian", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Huang, Zhi", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Henry, Andrew J", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Weiss, Daniel J", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Brady, Oliver J", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kraemer, Moritz UG", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Smith, David L", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Moyes, Catherine L", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bhatt, Samir", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gething, Peter W", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Horby, Peter W", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bogoch, Isaac I", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Brownstein, John S", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mekaru, Sumiko R", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tatem, Andrew J", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Khan, Kamran", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hay, Simon I", 